43:47.720 --> 43:51.804
-Are you ready?
-[cheering, applause]

43:51.804 --> 43:53.345
All right, you guys.

43:53.345 --> 43:54.679
Here she is,

43:54.679 --> 43:56.303
-the name on everybody's lips.
-Water?

43:56.303 --> 43:57.512
You got this. You're Alice.

43:57.512 --> 43:59.053
You're the name
on everybody's lips.

43:59.053 --> 44:00.220
Alice!

44:00.220 --> 44:02.887
♪ riot grrrl music ♪

44:02.887 --> 44:05.095
-[cheering, applause]
-Hey!

44:05.095 --> 44:06.345
[whoops]

44:06.345 --> 44:08.011
[laughs]

44:08.011 --> 44:10.845
Hi. Thank you. Thank you.

44:10.845 --> 44:14.595
Thank you so much.
Please. Please, please, please.

44:14.595 --> 44:17.679
Thank you. Oh, it is so great
to be back.

44:17.679 --> 44:20.470
It really is. I have missed you
all so much.

44:20.470 --> 44:22.387
Uh-- that hiatus
was really long, wasn't it?

44:22.387 --> 44:24.679
Felt like it was, like,
a decade or something. Huh?

44:24.679 --> 44:26.303
-Right, Heather?
-[Heather] Sure did.

44:26.303 --> 44:28.261
Yeah, oh, you met
my third cousin?

44:28.261 --> 44:30.345
-Yes. Ha.
-Yeah.

44:30.345 --> 44:31.470
[Alice]
And-- So how was your break?

44:31.470 --> 44:33.178
[Heather]
I was just hanging out

44:33.178 --> 44:35.220
in my, uh, shared studio
apartment in the Valley,

44:35.220 --> 44:37.011
just waiting for the show
to come back.

44:37.011 --> 44:38.512
[chuckles]
Yeah. Is there a reason

44:38.512 --> 44:40.303
you keep bringing up
that you share an apartment?

44:40.303 --> 44:42.220
-[laughter]
-[Heather] I just know that

44:42.220 --> 44:44.220
you have an extra bedroom
at your house

44:44.220 --> 44:46.970
-and it's real fancy.
-[laughs] Okay. Oh...

44:46.970 --> 44:48.470
No, I get it.

44:48.470 --> 44:49.720
[both]
See you latte.

44:49.720 --> 44:50.970
[laughter]

44:50.970 --> 44:54.553
All right, ladies and gentlemen
and everyone in between,

44:54.553 --> 44:56.887
it is my absolute pleasure
to welcome

44:56.887 --> 44:59.720
my dear friend and candidate
for L.A. mayor--

44:59.720 --> 45:03.178
she likes her coffee black
with one raw sugar--

45:03.178 --> 45:04.762
Bette Porter!

45:04.762 --> 45:07.804
[cheering, applause]

45:07.804 --> 45:09.720
[Sharon Jones's
"Matter of Time" playing]

45:09.720 --> 45:13.387
♪ Oh, yeah, oh, yeah,
oh, yeah ♪

45:13.387 --> 45:15.470
♪ Oh, yeah,
oh, yeah, oh, yeah ♪

45:15.470 --> 45:18.261
♪ Uh-huh, oh, yeah... ♪

45:18.261 --> 45:21.804
Wow. Well, thank you
so much for coming.

45:21.804 --> 45:24.720
-Thank you for having me.
-Uh, full disclosure,

45:24.720 --> 45:27.053
we've known each other
for about 25 years.

45:27.053 --> 45:29.095
[sighs]
Yes, that's right.

45:29.095 --> 45:32.679
Okay, and in those 25 years,
have I ever gone easy on you?

45:32.679 --> 45:34.595
Cut you any slack?

45:34.595 --> 45:35.595
-Let you off the hook?
-Not even for

45:35.595 --> 45:37.261
-a single day, Alice.
-Yeah. Okay.

45:37.261 --> 45:41.679
So, do your voters know
that you stole a billboard

45:41.679 --> 45:42.845
-in the mid-aughts?
-[chuckles]

45:42.845 --> 45:45.720
-Uh, we-we borrowed it, Alice.
-[laughter]

45:45.720 --> 45:46.929
-Oh, "we."
-We borrowed it. Yeah.

45:46.929 --> 45:48.929
[Alice] Oh, you're put--
Okay. Okay. Were you gonna

45:48.929 --> 45:51.011
keep that on the DL?
Because I didn't get that memo.

45:51.011 --> 45:53.428
-I think we should. Yeah.
-Well, I missed that.

45:53.428 --> 45:55.387
[Alice]
All right, let's dig in.

45:55.387 --> 45:58.136
So, in case you've been
living under a rock,

45:58.136 --> 46:00.345
yesterday during a forum,

46:00.345 --> 46:03.720
a man who's since been
identified as Tyler Adams

46:03.720 --> 46:06.136
publicly accused
mayoral candidate Bette Porter

46:06.136 --> 46:08.679
of having an affair
with his wife.

46:08.679 --> 46:11.261
-Is that correct?
-That's correct.

46:11.261 --> 46:13.136
So why did you want
to come on the show today?

46:13.136 --> 46:14.970
I mean, why not
let something like that

46:14.970 --> 46:16.804
just kind of blow over?

46:16.804 --> 46:20.053
Well, because I won't
be shamed into silence.

46:20.053 --> 46:21.553
I mean, historically,

46:21.553 --> 46:23.387
that's what happens to women
in my position.

46:23.387 --> 46:26.637
We're shamed and then
we stand down, but I won't.

46:26.637 --> 46:28.470
-Not now, not ever.
-[audience cheering]

46:31.261 --> 46:32.804
[Alice]
So, are you sorry

46:32.804 --> 46:34.387
that you slept
with a married woman?

46:34.387 --> 46:37.470
Well, it's tricky
because I-I...

46:37.470 --> 46:40.387
I don't want anyone
to think that I'm okay

46:40.387 --> 46:43.470
with causing another person
pain, because I'm not.

46:43.470 --> 46:46.845
But I also don't want it
to seem like I'm apologizing

46:46.845 --> 46:49.470
for having a relationship
with a consenting adult

46:49.470 --> 46:51.011
because that's also a message

46:51.011 --> 46:52.387
that I'm not comfortable
sending.

46:52.387 --> 46:54.679
So you're not sorry?

46:55.845 --> 46:57.345
I think I answered
the question.

46:57.345 --> 46:59.220
It's not that that simple.

46:59.220 --> 47:00.679
Ugh.

47:00.679 --> 47:02.470
It's getting
a little hot in here.

47:02.470 --> 47:04.387
-[laughter]
-[grunts softly]

47:04.387 --> 47:07.512
Can I just tell you
the most frustrating part

47:07.512 --> 47:09.428
of this whole ordeal?

47:09.428 --> 47:11.553
-Please.
-[sighs]

47:11.553 --> 47:13.845
I mean, it's
distracting.

47:13.845 --> 47:16.011
People would rather focus
on what's titillating

47:16.011 --> 47:17.887
than stare death in the face.

47:17.887 --> 47:22.970
And the fact is, our city is
in crisis and people are dying.

47:22.970 --> 47:24.845
[Alice]
I know

47:24.845 --> 47:28.470
that you have a very real
reason that you're running.

47:28.470 --> 47:31.470
A very personal reason.

47:31.470 --> 47:33.553
Why won't you talk about it?

47:33.553 --> 47:35.387
♪ somber music ♪

47:35.387 --> 47:37.637
♪♪♪

47:37.637 --> 47:39.512
Um,

47:39.512 --> 47:42.887
because despite
this week's events,

47:42.887 --> 47:46.220
I've chosen to keep
my private life private.

47:47.929 --> 47:50.011
But those people out there,

47:50.011 --> 47:54.011
they want to know who you are,

47:54.011 --> 47:56.345
not just what you stand for.

47:56.345 --> 47:58.220
[Bette]
Okay.

47:58.220 --> 48:00.595
Well, um...

48:00.595 --> 48:02.887
I'm a woman.

48:02.887 --> 48:05.762
I'm gay, I'm biracial.

48:05.762 --> 48:08.261
Um, I'm a mother

48:08.261 --> 48:10.095
to an extraordinary daughter.

48:10.095 --> 48:12.804
I'm an ex-wife, uh, a friend.

48:12.804 --> 48:14.053
I think I'm a really
loyal friend.

48:14.053 --> 48:15.679
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah.

48:15.679 --> 48:18.053
[Bette]
Uh, I'm a daughter,

48:18.053 --> 48:20.845
I'm-I'm a sister.

48:20.845 --> 48:23.929
Uh... and I'm...

48:26.970 --> 48:29.512
...and I'm you.

48:29.512 --> 48:31.929
I'm-- I am a part of you.

48:31.929 --> 48:34.053
I really feel that.

48:34.053 --> 48:38.804
You know, I'm that part of you
that wants to do better.

48:38.804 --> 48:41.762
I'm that part of you
that loves this city

48:41.762 --> 48:46.095
and wants to see all
of its communities thrive.

48:47.637 --> 48:52.804
I'm that part of you
that makes mistakes.

48:56.011 --> 48:58.637
And I know I've disappointed
people that I love.

48:58.637 --> 49:02.595
And that's not a mistake
that I want to make again.

49:02.595 --> 49:05.804
And I hope
that my indiscretions

49:05.804 --> 49:08.637
don't cloud my greater purpose,

49:08.637 --> 49:10.929
because while I know

49:10.929 --> 49:14.762
[exhales]
I'm not the perfect messenger,

49:14.762 --> 49:17.970
I do have the perfect message.

49:22.595 --> 49:24.345
[applause swells]

49:24.345 --> 49:26.095
[audience cheering]

49:26.095 --> 49:27.970
Thank you.

49:31.595 --> 49:33.136
[Alice]
Thank you.

49:33.136 --> 49:35.011
Thank you.

